byline.contributor: Majd Al-Waheidi contributed reporting from Gaza City, and Myra Noveck from Jerusalem.

abstract: Israeli navy stops ship carrying pro-Palestinian activists heading for Gaza Strip, thwarting attempted protest against Israel's control of people and material in and out of Gaza.
lead_paragraph: The vessel, which was going to protest a maritime blockade on the coastal enclave, was being led to the southern Israeli port of Ashdod, a military statement said.

headline.main: Israeli Navy Intercepts Ship in Flotilla Sailing Toward Gaza Strip
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Middle East; Israel: Ship Halted in Blockade Protest
